The original site of the school is located in [[Huludao|Huludao]] [[Lianshan|Lianshan]] Xinhua Street, covering an area of 39000 square meters and a construction area of more than 20000 square meters. There are teaching buildings, office buildings, experimental audio-visual education buildings, dormitory buildings, canteens, small courts, garden communities, etc.
At the end of 2004, the school moved into a brand-new school site in the [[Longgang_District|Longgang District]] Education Park. It is located at the junction of Lianshan District, Longgang District. The history of Huludao No. 1 senior high school has opened a new chapter.

The school was founded in 1935 and entered the era of new China with the liberation of Northeast China in 1948. Huludao was the first batch of key senior middle schools in Liaoning Province in the 1960s;
